%p
  The University of Michigan also complies with the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA), which prohibits the release of education records without student permission. Although FERPA regulations apply only to U-M students, The University of Michigan is equally committed to protecting the privacy of all visitors to our Web site.
